<br>
Greetings all, it's the Bear, er Brelkeryn, seeking to put together a raid to head down into the Hole to hit the various rare types of fish, er epic quest mobs along the way.<br>
<br>
After monitoring these forums for the past few weeks I have noticed that The Hole doesn't seem to have many open raids, so let's see what we can do about planning one.<br>
<br>
The only epic piece I would like to &quot;claim&quot; is the first Kirn drop, depending on how things go we may be down there long enough to wait for him to respawn and kill him again.<br>
<br>
I am familiar with the location of Kirn, Kindle (Enchanter epic), and the Paladin epic mob, as well as roughly where the ranger epic mob is.  I have not participated in combats with these mobs directly, but I am familiar with tower attack plans and a number of the other mobs in the area.<br>
<br>
All other epic pieces will be randomed out based on who is on the raid that needs the piece.  If we can get a 55 mage (or higher) to come with us on the raid, and take one for the team (see below), I would not be opposed to giving the mage's designee a double chance on an item.  Any other items that we loot along the way are NBG, with any gems or coins going to cover raid costs and spellcasters with costly components.<br>
<br>
I will bring several stacks of peridots with me as well as several stacks of pearls for Call of the Hero.<br>
<br>
What I forsee we need to make this raid a reality happen is a cleric for each group, three or maybe four at the most groups of 50+ folks. Required participants to make this happen:<br>
<br>
55+ Monk for pulling, ideally with experience with this zone.<br>
55+ Enchanter for crowd control.<br>
55+ Mage with Call of the Hero<br>
Two 50+ wizards or druids for evacs.<br>
One Cleric per group, preferably the higher level the better.<br>
Large mix of melee types (ideally in the 50+ range).<br>
<br>
Plan to meet inside the dungeon on the entry ramp at 7pm, with a goal of having groups formed and setting out around 7:30pm.<br>
<br>
To gain entry to the Hole you will require one of the following:<br>
<br>
1. A kind rogue who can pick the lock on the rock.<br>
2. Swim between the cracks, shrink potion required for a large race, small races can make it through without a problem, not sure about medium size races.<br>
3. A Hole key available in Paineel, slaughter tons of kobolds in the Warrens for faction to not be KOS in the city, be evil and liked there, or let an Enchanter in the city to purchase the no drop key to allow you in.<br>
<br>
From what I've experienced there are two strategies for Hole epic raids:<br>
<br>
Strategy 1 involves fighting your way deep inside the dungeon stopping at various resting points along the way and then finally arriving at either the dock area where people swim and leap off the water fall down to where Master Yael spawns which can result in deaths due to lag, or worse if Yael is up, or fighting back to the Undead Tower passing the Ranger epic mob along the way.  I plan to check to see the status of Yael prior to starting the raid, so I'll let everyone know the plan as we are getting started.<br>
<br>
Pros:<br>
1. XP along the way.<br>
2. Potential for loot along the way.<br>
<br>
Cons:<br>
1. High risk if the groups aren't balanced from the hard hitting mobs along the way.<br>
2. Slow development of the raid, long fight to get to the tower.<br>
3. Lack of personal experience fighting back to the tower, would need someone with knowledge of the safe areas along the way.<br>
<br>
Strategy 2 involves finding a brave 55 mage who wants to take one for the team.  This person groups with the raid leader at the entrance, dies due to drowning, etc, and then a 1st-level rogue drags their body back to the ledge near the undead tower, where they are rezzed either by a rez stick, rez goo, or a dwarven cleric of brel who takes the leap down the huge hole near the zone border to Paineel with their invulnerability spells up.  People ITU up before being summoned by the mage and then people proceed into the tower.  This is my preferred method of approach as it allow us to get quickly back to the meaty part of the quest.<br>
<br>
Pros:<br>
1. Speed<br>
2. Less risk from agro death along the way.<br>
3. Greater amount of time trying for the epic pieces.<br>
<br>
Cons:<br>
1. The poor mage must die and get a low xp rez.<br>
2. Requires access to a dwarven cleric who has not ruined his Hole faction, a rez staff, or rez good.  (None of which are immediately available.)<br>
<br>
Anyway folks, if this sounds like something that is of interest to you, I am giving preference to those that can bring themselves and a group of talented folks with them to make this happen.<br>
<br>
I am open to suggestions for changes of requirements and the like, and if you have experience in the Hole send me a tell in game or post here and I will contact you so we can suck out your brain, er draw upon your knowledge.<br>
<br>
See you there, hopefully this will be the first raid of many!<br>
<br>
Regards,<br>
